amic report is looking for reflection on Constructor.newInstance for a specific test class, suggesting that metadata has been generated by an agent. I wonder if static initialization happens at runtime in the Native image. Let's think this through!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering build.gradle properties**\\n\\nI'm thinking about adding a system property in the build.gradle tasks, maybe for the native image runtime. The property's value needs a temporary directory, perhaps a constant like \\\"build/cglib-debug.\\\" But I could also make it dynamic. I’m considering using `tasks.withType(Test)` to set the system property for \\\"cglib.debugLocation\\\" to the absolute path of \\\"cglib-debug.\\\" For native tests, I wonder if the TCK plugin needs the test runtime? I'll look into other projects for how they manage system properties.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ySDJpeT1J1NgIos2C8GipwfC|fc_0915a4173ec1635b0169f5ab53350481909bdbf5e96f5d1abc", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"systemProperty|jvmArgs|runtimeArgs|cglib.debugLocation\" tests/src -n | head -100"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 716, "output": 1064, "cacheRead": 16896, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 18676, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777707842926, "responseId": "resp_0915a4173ec1635b0169f5ab4344d08190b95e01ab6a7a7d96"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_ySDJpeT1J1NgIos2C8GipwfC|fc_0915a4173ec1635b0169f5ab53350481909bdbf5e96f5d1abc", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/javax.activation/activation/1.1/build.gradle:31:        jvmArgs += [\"-Djava.security.manager=allow\"]\ntests/src/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-gson/0.12.0/build.gradle:21:    jvmArgs += [\ntests/src/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-jackson/0.12.0/build.gradle:47:    jvmArgs '--add-exports', 'java.base/sun.security.uti