variables.\\n\\nI’m concerned about the static fallback handling runtime issues versus build-time. If the DebuggingClassWriter class is initialized during the analysis due to reflection, I wonder if there’s a reflection config for its constructor. It seems like CGLIB code might show up in tests but wouldn't execute during analysis, so that should be okay.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused coverage for `org.springframework.cglib.core.DebuggingClassWriter$1`.\n\nChanges:\n- Added dedicated test file:\n  - `tests/src/org.springframework/spring-core/5.3.15/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_core/DebuggingClassWriterAnonymous1Test.java`\n- Added a minimal test-scope `TraceClassVisitor` shim so `DebuggingClassWriter`’s optional ASM trace path is active and reaches `Constructor#newInstance(...)`:\n  - `tests/src/org.springframework/spring-core/5.3.15/src/test/java/org/springframework/asm/util/TraceClassVisitor.java`\n- Updated Spring Core test Gradle config to enable `cglib.debugLocation` for JVM and Native Image test execution:\n  - `tests/src/org.springframework/spring-core/5.3.15/build.gradle`\n\nThe new test uses the public `DebuggingClassWriter` API to generate bytecode, verifies the generated `.class` bytes, and verifies the `.asm` trace file is written, which exercises the remaining dynamic-access call site.\n\nPer instruction, I did not compile or run the tests.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0915a4173ec1635b0169f5ac315c9881908e83e147026932e8\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 431, "output": 929, "cacheRead": 26624, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27984, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777708070837, "responseId": "resp_0915a4173ec1635b0169f5ac2764a88190897be9b885ea8560"}, "toolResults": []}
